# laken project defaults

## Where to work

- Run commands from the repo root (`pyproject.toml`, `uv.lock`).
- Edit source under `src/` and `tests/` only.

## uv workflow (WSL / Unix venv)

This repo uses a **Unix-style** `.venv` (`bin/`, `lib/`, often `lib64/` on Linux). That is the intended layout.

On a Windows host, the project path is usually `/mnt/c/Users/.../laken` in **WSL bash**. Run **all** `uv` commands there ‚Äî not from PowerShell or cmd.

- `uv sync` before the first `uv run ‚Ä¶` in a session and after dependency changes.
- Use `uv run <tool>` (pytest, ruff, python, ‚Ä¶). Do not use `pip install -e .` unless the user asks.
- Dev dependencies (`pytest`, `ruff`) live in `[dependency-groups] dev` in `pyproject.toml`.
- From Windows automation (Cursor agent shell), use WSL only: `wsl -e bash -lc 'cd /mnt/c/.../laken && uv ‚Ä¶'`.
- **Never** run `uv sync`, `uv run`, or `uv run python .cursor/scripts/...` from PowerShell on `C:\...` ‚Äî even one command can corrupt or replace the Unix `.venv`.
- `.cursor/scripts/*.py` call WSL when launched from Windows Python, but prefer `wsl ‚Ä¶ && uv run pytest` directly to avoid Windows `uv` touching the project first.

## Virtual environment ‚Äî do not destroy

**Never delete or recreate `.venv`** unless the user explicitly asks in the current message.

Forbidden without explicit user request:

- `Remove-Item -Recurse .venv`, `rm -rf .venv`, or any command that removes the `.venv` directory
- `uv venv --clear`, or ‚Äúfixing‚Äù sync by wiping `.venv`

If `uv sync` fails (e.g. `failed to remove file .venv\lib64` or `Lib` access denied):

1. Stop ‚Äî do not delete `.venv`.
2. Report the error. Likely cause: `uv` was run from the **wrong shell** (PowerShell vs WSL).
3. User recreates from WSL only: `rm -rf .venv && uv sync` in bash under `/mnt/c/.../laken`.

**Wrong layout:** `.venv/Scripts/` and `.venv/Lib/` with `pyvenv.cfg` pointing at `cpython-*-windows-*` ‚Äî native Windows uv; not used for this project.

## Do not modify

- `.venv/` (no deletes, no edits inside), `dist/`, `build/`, `*.egg-info/`
- `.pytest_cache/`, `.ruff_cache/`
- Local lakehouse / Spark artifact dirs (see `.gitignore`)

## Style and changes

- Match Ruff settings in `pyproject.toml`: line length 100, target `py311`, rules E/F/I/UP/B/SIM.
- Prefer minimal, focused diffs; no drive-by refactors.
- Do not add comments or docstrings unless the user asks.

## Tests by area

- Changes under `src/laken/deploy/` ‚Üí run at least `uv run pytest tests/deploy -q` (via WSL on Windows hosts).
- Broader lakehouse changes ‚Üí `uv run pytest` (full suite).

See `AGENTS.md` for the repository map and command table.
